        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>United States Representative on the Council of the Organization of American States, with personal rank of Ambassador, from January 7, 1951.</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1952-54v04/persons#p_DJC1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="2">
            <p>U.S. Representative with personal rank of Ambassador to the Council of the OAS until May 15, 1956; thereafter, Acting Director, Office of Inter-American Regional Political Affairs, Bureau of Inter-American Affairs, Department of State</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1955-57v06/persons#p_DJC1</source-url>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1955-57v07/persons#p_DJC1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Representative to the Council of the Organization of American States; concurrently Acting Director of the Office of Inter–American Regional Political Affairs, Bureau of Inter–American Affairs, Department of State, from May 15, 1956</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1955-57v11/persons#p_DJC1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Acting Director, Office of Inter-American Regional Political Affairs, Bureau of Inter-American Affairs, Department of State, until January 1960</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1958-60v02/persons#p_DJC3</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Acting Director, Office of Inter-American Regional Political Affairs, Department of State, until January 1960; Representative to the Council of the Organization of American States until November 12, 1960; Chairman, Inter-American Peace Committee, August 7, 1959–August 6, 1960</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1958-60v05/persons#p_DJC1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
